The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 01, 2004 				 VIP group plant in Himachal Pradesh
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 31: Microtex India Limited plans to set up a plant in Himachal Pradesh and has earmarked Rs 10 crore for the project.																								The new plant will increase our production capacity to 2 lakh units per month from the current level of 1.25 lakh units, Microtex India chief executive officer L. Vinaybhushan Reddy said. The company, which is part of the Rs 400-crore VIP group, has a plant in Bangalore at present.																								Livein  a brand of the company  will open three to four exclusive outlets in Calcutta in the next couple of years. Each outlet will need an investment of about Rs 25-30 lakh. At present, Live-in is available in 4,000 multi-brand outlets across the country.																								The brand has a turnover of Rs 60 crore with over 10 per cent being generated from the eastern region, which the company plans to increase to 15 per cent in two years.																								 The total marketing expenditure of the company stands at around 15 per cent of the turnover. 
